<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Cha_Tae-hyun" title="Cha Tae-hyun">Cha Tae-hyun</a> as Seung-ryong. A fan of the original comic, Tae-hyun stated at a press conference that he "cried [his] eyes out" when reading it. Rather than draw his inspiration from <a href="/wiki/Mentally_challenged" class="mw-redirect" title="Mentally challenged">mentally challenged</a> people in reality or as portrayed in other media, he felt it necessary to play the character as written in the comic. Cha gained eight <a href="/wiki/Kilogram" title="Kilogram">kilograms</a> during production, and was unable to lose all of that weight for his wedding in 2006.<sup id="cite_ref-Korea_Times_3-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Korea_Times-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>
<ul><li>Seo Dae-han as young Seung-ryong.</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ha_Ji-won" title="Ha Ji-won">Ha Ji-won</a> as Ji-ho. Playing the role of a frustrated pianist, Ji-won performed on the piano herself for the film. Although she had studied piano as a child, she received tutoring from singer/songwriter No Young-shim, who also taught her subtle gestures and postures.<sup id="cite_ref-Korea_Times_3-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Korea_Times-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Sulli_Choi" class="mw-redirect" title="Sulli Choi">Choi Sulli</a> as young Ji-ho.</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Park_Hee-soon" title="Park Hee-soon">Park Hee-soon</a> as Sang-soo.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Park_Ha-sun" title="Park Ha-sun">Park Ha-sun</a> as Ji-in.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Greena_Park" title="Greena Park">Greena Park</a> as Hee-yeong.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jeon_Mi-seon" title="Jeon Mi-seon">Jeon Mi-seon</a> as young Seung-ryong's mother.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Lee_Ki-young" title="Lee Ki-young">Lee Ki-young</a> as "Small Star" president.</li>
<li>Lee Sang-hoon as junk seller.</li></ul>
